result.execSummary:
The defendant Aubrey K. Pinager Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK] case called at 4:14pm.  (second hearing on this date)  
Defendant Aubrey K. Pinager in court, in custody, with Attorney Whitney Hagemann.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of " No Contest " entered on Counts #3, #4, #5, and 7; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses the remaining counts. 

On Count #3 the Court sentences Mr. Pinager to:
--serve 9 months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-release privileges; to commence forthwith 
--Mr. Pinager is required to serve this jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without illegal drugs in his system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber/Work release privileges without further process.
--pay costs, fees, assessments, surcharges;  this amount is to be converted to a civil judgment 
--Days credit for time served on this Count #3 jail term:  67 days 

On Counts #4 & #5 the Court withholds sentence and places Mr. Pinager on Probation for three years, consecutive to Count #3.
On Count #7 the Court withholds sentence and places Mr. Pinager on Probation for two years, also consecutive to Count #3.
Conditions of Probation on all three counts are:
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required by the Agent
--to complete a Certified Batteres Intervention Program
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program
--to maintain absolute sobriety: no possession or consumption of alcohol or illegal drugs
--no presence in bars or taverns or liquor stores
--contact with the victim, Amanda, only if both the victim and the Agent approve of such contact in advance
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon demand
--to pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges including the DNA surcharges; also to pay subpoena/summons fees of $33
